; redirector.test
;
; A heavy-CNAME / heavy-wildcard zone, modeled on what a
; URL shortener or CDN-fronted SaaS publishes. Almost
; every owner here is either a CNAME pointing somewhere
; else or a wildcard that catches every name under a
; subtree.
;
; Wildcards (RFC 4592) match every name that has no
; exact record at or above the wildcard owner. So a
; query for foo.t.redirector.test matches *.t but a
; query for tracking.foo.t.redirector.test does NOT
; match *.t -- it would need a *.foo.t to catch.
;
; Try in the demo: query bit.redirector.test for A
; (CNAME chase), then anything.t.redirector.test for A
; (wildcard expansion -- the response rewrites the
; wildcard owner to the queried name).
;
$ORIGIN redirector.test.
$TTL 600
@               IN  SOA   ns1.redirector.test. ops.redirector.test. (
                          2026010101 3600 1800 604800 86400 )
@               IN  NS    ns1.redirector.test.
ns1             IN  A     198.51.100.50
@               IN  A     198.51.100.50
www             IN  CNAME redirector.test.
api             IN  CNAME api-lb.redirector.test.
api-lb          IN  A     198.51.100.51
api-lb          IN  A     198.51.100.52
api-lb          IN  A     198.51.100.53
bit             IN  CNAME api.redirector.test.
go              IN  CNAME api.redirector.test.
short           IN  CNAME api.redirector.test.
*.t             IN  A     198.51.100.60
*.t             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:11::60
*.preview       IN  CNAME staging.redirector.test.
staging         IN  A     198.51.100.70
